<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><b><i>Quote:</i></b><hr> Fine give Warriors and every other class an ability which will do 7-15k pretty much unresistable damage once every 2 game days without the mob having a chance to respond and I will shut the hell up about it.<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
Actually, warriors had and still have the ability to do *200K* or so dmg in one round (with rampage and earthshaker + a 60ish mob AE pull and lucky procs...) AND we can do it every 10 minutes.  It's a situational use skill tho, not QUITE as generic as a big BOOM, but still in the same genre.  For a few weeks, warriors with that setup could rampage NONSTOP if they cared to abuse a bug (kudos for the lucky folks who could but didn't for reporting it Verant and getting it fixed, wonder why they haven't fixed chaincasting normally recast delayed spells that use the same bug after so many years...).<br>
<br>
We also get &quot;finishing blow&quot;, which while apparently level capped, does let us do 32k in one swat (like rogues/assassinate, tho they can to it to full health mobs...).  Several classes also have instant-poof abilities vs certain types of mobs (clerics vs. undead, or the unreal crits pallies with the AA get vs. them, etc.).<br>
<br>
MB *IS* argueably superior to those in PVP, but I'd still bet on the ranger with AM3, a pre-nerf bow of doom, trueshot and 14 damage arrows/endless quiver.  With 2k+ crits very possible AND 400ish range, rangers are the absolute bane of non horse-riding PVPers.<br>
<br>
Is it broken?  Yah, a bit, but most &quot;cool&quot; abilities are (almost by definition).  Is it unbalancing in PVP?  Yah, it'd suck to be MBed right off the bat (tho better than the damned rapture enchanters get imho).  Can it be used in unusual situations that weren't necessarily intended?  Yep, we got 10 or so MB wizzies now, I'm quite sure most kunark boss mobs were supposed to live more than 3 seconds.  <br>
<br>
But what the heck, in the end it's just a Big Nuke; back in the day, so was icecomet (which would kill most level 50's in one shot when it came out).  Not something to cry nerf about methinks.  The only real concern I have is that it'll deter/affect &quot;good&quot; small group encounters in PoPo (pronouced &quot;PooPoo&quot; btw, until proven different <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START ;) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/wink.gif ALT=";)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  ) by setting a minimum hp for decent loot mobs to 100k or so+.<br>
<br>
Just my thoughts anyway.  It's a cool ability, would hate to see the wizzies lose it, cause if I was one I'd want it too. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START ;) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/wink.gif ALT=";)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->   Hrm... maybe verant will put in a &quot;health burn&quot; effect for warriors... at 8k+ hp for the well-geared, that'd be pretty impressive. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START ;) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/wink.gif ALT=";)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
RdT.<br>
